 exploitation of people for profit? </p><p><strong>Annie Kelly</strong> hears guests including: <strong><a href=\"http://iloblog.org/2012/11/30/labour-trafficking-a-real-eye-opener/beate-andrees/\">Beate Andrees</a></strong>, head of the programme to combat forced labour at the <a href=\"http://www.ilo.org/global/lang--en/index.htm\">ILO</a>; <strong>Romana Cacchioli</strong>, of <a href=\"http://www.antislavery.org/english/\">Anti-Slavery International;</a> <strong>Andrew Wallis</strong>, chief executive of <a href=\"http://www.unseenuk.org/\">Unseen</a>; <strong>Leonardo Sakamoto</strong>, who covers slavery for <a href=\"http://reporterbrasil.org.br/http://\">Reporter Brazil</a>, and a first-hand testimony from a Chinese person who has experience trafficking.</p><p>• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/global-development/2013/apr/08/talk-point-modern-day-slavery\">Relive the debates on our talk point</a></p><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/anniekelly\">Annie Kelly</a></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/matt-hill\">Matt Hill</a></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/lucy-lamble\">Lucy Lamble</a></div><br/><p style=\"clear:both\" />" "http://www.guardian.co.uk/global-development/audio/2013/apr/18/global-development-podcast-modern-day-slavery" (20847 48288) old 30 nil nil ((title nil "Global development podcast: modern-day slavery in focus") (link nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/global-development/audio/2013/apr/18/global-development-podcast-modern-day-slavery") (description nil "<p>The UN's International Labour Organisation (ILO) estimates that 21 million people around the world are engaged in forced labour, but what are the causes and consequences of this modern-day form of slavery?</p><p>How far is globalised trade driving modern slavery as it increases the demand for ever-cheaper goods? Why does slavery still exist almost 150 years after most countries abolished it? And what should governments do now to tackle the trafficking and exploitation of people for profit? </p><p><strong>Annie Kelly</strong> hears guests including: <strong><a href=\"http://iloblog.org/2012/11/30/labour-trafficking-a-real-eye-opener/beate-andrees/\">Beate Andrees</a></strong>, head of the programme to combat forced labour at the <a href=\"http://www.ilo.org/global/lang--en/index.htm\">ILO</a>; <strong>Romana Cacchioli</strong>, of <a href=\"http://www.antislavery.org/english/\">Anti-Slavery International;</a> <strong>Andrew Wallis</strong>, chief executive of <a href=\"http://www.unseenuk.org/\">Unseen</a>; <strong>Leonardo Sakamoto</strong>, who covers slavery for <a href=\"http://reporterbrasil.org.br/http://\">Reporter Brazil</a>, and a first-hand testimony from a Chinese person who has experience trafficking.</p><p>• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/global-development/2013/apr/08/talk-point-modern-day-slavery\">Relive the debates on our talk point</a></p><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/anniekelly\">Annie Kelly</a></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/matt-hill\">Matt Hill</a></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/lucy-lamble\">Lucy Lamble</a></div><br/><p style=\"clear:both\" />") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/global-development")) "Global development") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "Slavery") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/law")) "Human trafficking") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/publication")) "guardian.co.uk") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/tone")) "Editorial") (pubDate nil "Thu, 18 Apr 2013 09:28:00 GMT") (guid nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/global-development/audio/2013/apr/18/global-development-podcast-modern-day-slavery") (dc:creator nil "Annie Kelly, Matt Hill, Lucy Lamble") (dc:subject nil "Global development") (dc:date nil "2013-04-19T09:44:35Z") (dc:type nil "Audio") (dc:identifier nil "407097908") (media:keywords nil "Global development, Slavery, Human trafficking") (media:content ((height . "84") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "140") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Environment/Pix/columnists/2012/11/19/1353339895093/MDG--Benin--Slave-child-a-011.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Alamy") (media:description nil "Child slaves works as in the forge in Dan Tokpa market Cotouno hidden away in a corner of this foul and sprawling market with boys as young as five toil in the festering heat, in Benin, West Africa Photograph: Alamy")) (media:content ((duration . "2155") (fileSize . "34639318") (type . "audio/mpeg") (url . "http://download.guardian.co.uk/audio/kip/global-development/series/modern-day-slavery-in-focus/1366209919622/4694/gdn.glo.130419.mh.slavery-modern-focus.mp3"))))) ("[COULD NOT DOWNLOAD HEADLINES!]" "viernes, 08:26: Newsticker could not retrieve news from Law | guardian.co.uk.
